ft|\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagdeco|ENG}} Chelsea\n| 19 December 2015\n| 15 May 2016\n{{WDL|27|10|11|6|for=53|against=34|diff=yes}}\n|align=left|\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagdeco|CHN}} [[China national under-23 football team|China U-21/U-23]]\n| 10 September 2018\n| 20 September 2019\n{{WDL|6|3|3|0|for=18|against=4|diff=yes}}\n|align=left|\n|-\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Total\n{{WDLtot|816|466|178|172|for=1630|against=797|diff=yes}}\n!\n|}\n\n==Honours and achievements==\n\n===Player===\n\n'''De Graafschap'''\n* [[Tweede Divisie]] (1): [[Tweede Divisie 1968\u201369|1969]]\n\n'''San Jose Earthquakes'''\n* [[North American Soccer League (1968\u20131984)|North American Soccer League]] Southern Division (1): [[1977 North American Soccer League season|1977]] (Runner-up)\n\n===Manager===\n\n;Individual\n* [[Asian Football Confederation#AFC Coach of the Year|AFC Coach of the Year]] (1): [[Asian Football Confederation#AFC Coach of the Year|2002]]\n* [[World Soccer (magazine)#World Manager of the Year|World Soccer World Manager of the Year]] (1): 2002\n* Dutch Sports Coach of the Year (all sports) (2): 2002, 2005\n* [[Rinus Michels Award]] (2): [[Rinus Michels Award#Winners professional manager of the year|2005]], [[Rinus Michels Award#Winners professional manager of the year|2006]]\n* Coach of the Year in Russia (1): 2008<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hln.be/hln/nl/950/Buitenlands-Voetbal/article/detail/558522/2008/12/17/Hiddink-en-Advocaat-coach-van-het-jaar-in-Rusland.dhtml|title=Hiddink en Advocaat coach van het jaar in Rusland|work=HLN|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121006011358/http://www.hln.be/hln/nl/950/Buitenlands-Voetbal/article/detail/558522/2008/12/17/Hiddink-en-Advocaat-coach-van-het-jaar-in-Rusland.dhtml|archivedate=6 October 2012}}</ref>\n* In 2005 Hiddink received an honorary doctorate by the [[University of Seoul]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.omroepgelderland.nl/web/nieuwsartikel/94479/Guus-Hiddink-ontvangt-eredoctoraat.htm|archive-url=https://archive.is/20120906121215/http://www.omroepgelderland.nl/web/nieuwsartikel/94479/Guus-Hiddink-ontvangt-eredoctoraat.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=6 September 2012|title=Omroep Gelderland  \u2013 Nieuws \u2013 Guus Hiddink ontvangt eredoctoraat|author=Omroep Gelderland|work=omroepgelderland.nl}}</ref>\n* The [[De Graafschap]] [[mascot]] is named Guus in honor of Hiddink who was previously associated with the team as a player and as a manager.\n* The [[Gwangju World Cup Stadium]] was renamed the [[Guus Hiddink Stadium]] in honor of Hiddink's performance at the 2002 FIFA World Cup.\n* Hiddink was named an [[Citizenship#Honorary citizenship|honorary citizen]] of [[Seoul]] after reaching the 2002 FIFA World Cup semi-finals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://krant.telegraaf.nl/krant/archief/20020627/teksten/spo.hiddink.ereburger.bondscoach.html|title=De Telegraafi [] Telesport \u2013 Guus Hiddink ereburger|work=De Telegraaf}}</ref>\n* Hiddink was named an [[Citizenship#Honorary citizenship|honorary citizen]] of [[Eindhoven]] after winning his sixth Eredivisie title with PSV in 2006.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.trouw.nl/tr/nl/4324/nieuws/article/detail/1449056/2006/04/09/Guus-Hiddink-ereburger-van-Eindhoven.dhtml|title=Guus Hiddink ereburger van Eindhoven|work=Trouw}}</ref>\n* Hiddink was put on a stamp by [[Australia Post]] following the 2006 FIFA World Cup.\n* Hiddink was given a lifetime achievement award by the [[Royal Dutch Football Association]] in 2007. It was only the third such award ever given following those received by [[Rinus Michels]] and [[Johan Cruijff]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbalnieuws/75674/na-michels-en-cruijff-krijgt-ook-hiddink-oeuvreprijs/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120402104147/http://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbalnieuws/75674/na-michels-en-cruijff-krijgt-ook-hiddink-oeuvreprijs/|archivedate=2 April 2012|title=Na Michels en Cruijff krijgt ook Hiddink oeuvreprijs|publisher=fcupdate.nl|date=3 September 2007|accessdate=12 May 2014}}</ref>\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n;Club honours\n'''PSV Eindhoven'''\n* [[Eredivisie]]: [[Eredivisie 1986-87|1986\u201387]], [[Eredivisie 1987-88|1987\u201388]], [[Eredivisie 1988-89|1988\u201389]], [[Eredivisie 2002-03|2002\u201303]], [[Eredivisie 2004-05|2004\u201305]], [[Eredivisie 2005-06|2005\u201306]]\n* [[KNVB Cup]]: [[1987-88 KNVB Cup|1987\u201388]], [[1988-89 KNVB Cup|1988\u201389]], [[1989-90 KNVB Cup|1989\u201390]], [[2004-05 KNVB Cup|2004\u201305]]\n* [[European Cup]]: [[1987-88 European Cup|1987\u201388]]\n\n'''Real Madrid'''\n* [[Intercontinental Cup (football)|Intercontinental Cup]]: [[1998 Intercontinental Cup|1998]]\n\n'''Chelsea'''\n* [[F.A. Cup|FA Cup]]: [[2008\u201309 FA Cup|2008\u201309]]\n\n;International honours\n'''Netherlands'''\n* [[1998 FIFA World Cup]]: [[1998 FIFA World Cup#Third place match|Fourth place]]\n\n'''South Korea'''\n* [[2002 FIFA World Cup]]: [[2002 FIFA World Cup#Third place match|Fourth place]]\n\n'''Australia'''\n*[[2006 FIFA World Cup]]: Round of 16\n\n'''Russia'''\n* [[UEFA Euro 2008]]: [[UEFA Euro 2008 knockout stage#Russia vs Spain|Semi-final]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{S-ach}}\n{{succession box\n | before = {{flagicon|France}} [[Aim\u00e9 Jacquet]]\n |  after = {{flagicon|Germany}} [[J\u00fcrgen Klinsmann]]\n |  title = [[FIFA World Cup]] host country managers\n |  years = 2002 (with co-host {{flagicon|Japan}} [[Philippe Troussier]] (<small>{{flag|France}}</small>))\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n==References==\n{{notelist}}\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n'''Bibliography'''\n* Marc Bennetts, 'Football Dynamo&nbsp;\u2014 Modern Russia and the People's Game,' Virgin Books, (15 May 2008), 0753513196\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons}}\n* [http://www.guushiddink.nl Guus Hiddink Foundation]\n* {{BDFutbol manager|3059}}\n* [http://www.mackolik.com/Manager/Default.aspx?id=235 Managerial career] at Mackolik.com {{in lang|tr}}\n\n{{Navboxes colour\n|bg=Gold\n|bordercolor=Black\n|title=Awards \n|fg=Black\n|list1=\n{{UEFA Champions League